HEADER: Martins (2016) - There is no place for markedness in biologically-informed phonology
TITLE: There is no place for markedness in biologically-informed phonology
AUTHORTITLE: Martins (2016)
RAWAUTHORS: <a href="http://ling.auf.net/lingbuzz/003372?_s=xutbnkqscrEjY6qf&amp;_k=8u4ws9CB8S0JYnzw&amp;1">Pedro Tiago Martins</a>
AUTHORS: Pedro Tiago Martins
LASTNAMES: Martins
MONTH: December
YEAR: 2016
ABSTRACT: This chapter argues that markedness is not a useful concept (a position which has already been made clear in the literature before), and offers a few extra insights on why it should be abandoned if one is interested in phonology as (part of a) biological capacity.
